<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
The small town of Bree has had problems with thieves robbing people lately. The Mayor sets you on a quest to rid the town of the ruffians. This is a short quest that an experienced player can complete at <a class="nonexistent" href="./clvl">clvl</a> 1 with any character. <p>
The quest starts when you enter the yellow '&gt;' on the house in the middle of town. Upon entering the character appears in a locked room without his equipment. You can unpick the lock, and will be in a corridor. The last door down the corridor has you equipment on the floor. If you follow the path again past an open area you will find another door. Once this door is opened it aggravates all the monsters on the level, there is nothing you can do about that. Past the door are 5 novice rogues, one novice mage, one novice warrior and one bandit in small rooms. There is a guaranteed {good} dagger in the bandit's room (the second from the left in the top row) which the bandit may pick up. There is a second door, behind which is two more novice warriors. Once you have defeated all ten monsters a stairway appears in the bottom left of the map for you to leave by. 
</p>
<p>
A good tactic for those who do attempt this quest a <a class="nonexistent" href="./clvl">clvl</a> 1 is to set your tactics to running/berserker so that you can 'hack and back' the monsters with your extra speed to kill them. This is harder for mages, but still doable with your starting dagger. 
</p>
